==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔːntʃ|-ɔːntʃ]]

===Etymology===
From the [[w:French language|French]] ''[[pance]]'' from ''[[pancier]]'' meaning ''[[breastplate]]'' as worn by the Black Rider(s) or [[w:Polish language|Polish]] Pan Czerny of late medieval Poland.

===Noun===
'''paunch'''
# The stomach or abdomen of a human or animal, especially a large, protruding one.

===Related terms===
*[[paunchy]]

